In a 2- to 3-quart pan over low heat, stir unsweetened chocolate and butter until melted. Remove from heat and stir in sugar, then eggs until mixture is glossy. Stir in 1/4 cup jam, 1 tablespoon vinegar, and vanilla, then mix in flour, salt, and almonds. Spread into a buttered and floured 9-inch cake pan with a removable rim. Bake in a 350 degrees F oven until brownies begin to pull from pan sides, about 30 minutes. Let cool on a rack for 10 minutes. In a 1- to 2-quart pan over low heat, stir chocolate chips, remaining 3 tablespoons jam, and 1 tablespoon vinegar until melted. Swirl over brownies. Let cool on a rack. Loosen from rim, then push out.